  "prompt": "How does a TV channel earn money?",
  "response": "TV channels earn money through several primary revenue streams:\n\n1. Advertising\n- Selling commercial airtime to companies\n- Rates based on viewership and target audience\n- Different rates for prime time vs. off-peak hours\n\n2. Subscription Fees\n- Cable and satellite providers pay channels for the right to broadcast\n- Different channels have different carriage fees\n- Premium channels like HBO charge higher fees\n\n3. Sponsorships\n- Companies sponsor specific programs or segments\n- Product placements within shows\n- Branded content\n\n4. Syndication Rights\n- Selling rights to broadcast shows in different regions\n- Selling reruns to other networks\n\n5. Licensing\n- Selling content to streaming platforms\n- Selling international broadcasting rights\n- Merchandising related to popular shows\n\n6. Pay-Per-View Events\n- Charging viewers directly for special events like sports or concerts\n\n7. Digital Platforms\n- Online advertising\n- Streaming subscriptions\n- On-demand content monetization\n\nThe specific mix of revenue sources varies depending on the type of channel (broadcast, cable, premium) and its target audience.",
